# The Argument From Comfort

Living with a cat lowers measurable cortisol levels in humans. The presence of a purring cat is linked, in multiple longitudinal studies, to reduced incidence of stress-related cardiovascular events.

A cat is, in this sense, not just a companion but a low-cost preventive health intervention — one that arrives pre-trained, asks for very little, and lasts for fifteen years on average.

